<topic id="dcpp_how_to_place_cover_on_a_the_right_or_left_side">
    <title>How to Place Cover on the Right or Left Side</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm product="author developer editor authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"
          ><ph keyref="pdf-html5-transformation"/>
            <indexterm>Cover page<indexterm>Place cover on right
          side</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm product="author developer editor authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"
          ><ph keyref="pdf-html5-transformation"/>
            <indexterm>Cover page<indexterm>Place cover on left
          side</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm product="pdf-css ope">Cover page<indexterm>Place cover on right
          side</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm product="pdf-css ope">Cover page<indexterm>Place cover on left
          side</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
    <body>
        <p>In your <xref href="dcpp_the_customization_css.dita">customization CSS</xref>, add the
      following CSS rules:</p>
        <codeblock outputclass="language-css">*[class ~= "front-page/front-page"]{
    page-break-before:left;
}</codeblock>
        <note>This will create an empty page at the beginning of the publication, moving the cover content on the needed
            side.</note>
        <p>For more information, see: <xref
        href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-chemistry/topics/ch_controlling_page_breaks.html#ch_controlling_page_breaks"
        format="html" scope="external">Oxygen PDF Chemistry: Controlling Page Breaks</xref>.</p>
    </body>
